STEP 03: Select only the necessary continuous variables

dataset04 <- dataset04 %>%
  select(num_range("item_", 2:86, width = 2)) %>%  # item_03 ... item_86
  select(where(is.numeric))                         # keep continuous only

STEP 04. EFA with lavaan, testing factors from 1 to 8, per recommendation by earlier parallel analysis

STEP 07. Remove items with low loading, low communality, high complexity. Then save as a new dataset.

remove_items <- c(
  "item_02","item_06", "item_07","item_26","item_75")
# keep only items that actually exist (prevents errors)
remove_items <- intersect(remove_items, names(dataset04))
# create new dataset
dataset05 <- dataset04[, !names(dataset04) %in% remove_items]
# save as a new csv
write.csv(dataset05, "lar-china_test05_group_A_622_v0.csv", row.names = FALSE)
